{
  "texts": [
    "Das et al. [36] proposed an EEMD-ensemble CNN model that combines decomposed stock price signals, technical indicators, and Twitter (X) sentiment scores to improve stock price prediction accuracy.",
    "By integrating public sentiment through a dedicated CNN and leveraging multiple IMFbased subnetworks, the model outperforms baseline methods and highlights the value of social media data in financial forecasting.",
    "Liu [37] proposed a multimodal factor mining approach that combines market data, financial texts, and social media sentiment to enhance stock market forecasting accuracy and interpretability.",
    "Batra, Rakhi, and Daudpota [21] applied SVM to predict the sentiment of tweets about Apple from StockTwits, demonstrating a positive relationship between sentiments and stock price.",
    "Similarly, Nguyen, Thien, and Shirai [20] proposed Topic Sentiment Latent Dirichlet Allocation (TSLDA) to analyze social media sentiments, finding that incorporating sentiment data improves stock price predictions."
  ]
}